{"cells":[{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"# Lesson 3: Fetch Turbine Data ","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"This lesson covers how to fetch wind turbine data through the front end, so we can later plot it on the map. At the end of this lesson, you will have updated `WindTurbine.HomePage.tsx` to log `WindTurbine` records in the console.","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"### Learning Objectives","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"After completing this lesson, you will be able to:\n- Make requests to the backend to retrieve data.\n- Import modules from another file.","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"### Estimated time","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"This lab will take approximately **15 minutes** to complete.","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"### Lab Support","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"For support, check out the <a href=\"https://learn.c3.ai/page/help-center\" target=\"_blank\">Help Center</a> for  information.","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"-----","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"## Part 1: Generate application data\n\nIn this lesson, we make a request to retrieve turbine data. Run the following code snippet to populate the data model:","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":2,"languageId":"javascript","value":"// This method generates mock wind turbine data\nWindTurbine.dataGenerator()","output":[{"items":[{"mime":"text/plain","value":["Successfully created 50 wind turbines and 42 work orders with realistic data"]}]}],"executionSummary":{"timing":{"startTime":1780090909048,"endTime":1780090922096},"executionOrder":1,"success":true}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"The data generator should have created exactly 50 `WindTurbine` records.\n\nRun the following cell to verify the number of turbines generated:","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":2,"languageId":"javascript","value":"// Verify WindTurbine data is available \nWindTurbine.fetchCount()","output":[{"items":[{"mime":"text/plain","value":["50"]}]}],"executionSummary":{"timing":{"startTime":1780090970028,"endTime":1780090970498},"executionOrder":2,"success":true}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"-----","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"## Part 2: Fetch `WindTurbine` records\n\nThe `WindTurbine.fetch()` method makes a request to retrieve turbine data from the backend. On the front end, we emulate this behavior by making an HTTP request using the JavaScript [fetch](https://www.w3schools.com/jsref/api_fetch.asp) API. Alternatively, you can use other popular libraries such as [axios](https://axios-http.com/docs/intro) for handling HTTP requests.\n\nThe request endpoint follows the pattern `api/8/{TypeName}/{Operation}`. In this lesson, the we are fetching WindTurbine records, so the endpoint is `api/8/WindTurbine/fetch`.\n\nThe fetch method is already provided to you in <a href=\"../../ui/c3/src/components/CRUDMethods/WindTurbineCRUD.ts\"><code>ui/c3/src/components/CRUDMethods/WindTurbineCRUD.ts</code></a>. The following code snippet shows the `fetchAllTurbines` command:","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":2,"languageId":"javascript","value":"/*\n  ui/c3/src/components/CRUDMethods/WindTurbineCRUD.ts\n*/\nexport const fetchAllTurbines = async (): Promise<any[]> => {\n  const response = await fetch('api/8/WindTurbine/fetch', { // the endpoint follows the pattern /api/8/{TypeName}/{Operation}\n    method: 'POST', // WindTurbine.fetch uses POST method\n    headers: {\n      'Content-Type': 'application/json', // specify JSON content type\n    },\n    body: JSON.stringify({}), // WindTurbine.fetch() does not require any parameters\n  });\n\n  if (!response.ok) {\n    throw new Error('Network response was not ok');\n  }\n\n  const data = await response.json(); // parse JSON response\n  return data.objs || [];\n};","output":[{"items":[{"mime":"text/plain","value":["\u001b[31m---------------------------------------------------------------------------\u001b[0m","Internal Java error: SyntaxError: identifier is a reserved word: export (eval code#1(eval)#4)!"]}]}],"executionSummary":{"timing":{"startTime":1780091009729,"endTime":1780091009896},"executionOrder":3,"success":false}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"-----","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"## Part 3: Fetch turbines on page load\n\nFetch turbines when the page first renders by calling `fetchAllTurbines()` inside a React [useEffect](https://react.dev/reference/react/useEffect) hook.\n\nThe UI framework provides path aliases. Imports start with `@c3/app/ui/src/*`. The C3 bundler merges the `ui/c3/src` folders across your application package and its dependencies, and this alias points to this merged folder. For example, if you have a dependency on some package called `pkgB` and you want to use `ComponentB` from `pkgB`, you can import it from anywhere with the alias: \n\n```tsx\nimport ComponentB from '@c3/app/ui/src/ComponentB';\n```\n\nThis lets you import files without using relative paths to components in your application and enables easy access to components and functions across dependencies.\n\nNavigate to <a href=\"../../ui/c3/src/customInstances/WindTurbine.HomePage.tsx\"><code>WindTurbine.HomePage.tsx</code></a> and add the following imports:","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":2,"languageId":"javascript","value":"/* \n  WindTurbine.HomePage.tsx\n*/\n\n// import React from 'react';\n// import { MapContainer, TileLayer, ZoomControl } from 'react-leaflet';\n// import 'leaflet/dist/leaflet.css';\n// import '@c3/ui/WindTurbine.scss'; // Custom styles for this application\nimport { fetchAllTurbines } from '@c3/app/ui/src/components/CRUDMethods/WindTurbineCRUD';\nimport { useEffect } from 'react';","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"Now, we can write code to fetch `WindTurbine` data when the <code>WindTurbine.HomePage.tsx</code> component first loads.\n\nCopy the following code snippet into <a href=\"../../ui/c3/src/customInstances/WindTurbine.HomePage.tsx\"><code>WindTurbine.HomePage.tsx</code></a>. Place this method above the return statement and below the component’s top-level declarations.","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":2,"languageId":"javascript","value":"// WindTurbine.HomePage.tsx\n\n//const WindTurbineHomePage = () => {\n\n  useEffect(() => {\n      // Fetch wind turbine data using CRUD method\n      const loadTurbines = async () => {\n        try {\n          const turbineData = await fetchAllTurbines();\n          console.log('Success:', turbineData);\n        } catch (error) {\n          console.error('Error fetching wind turbine data:', error);\n        } \n      };\n\n      loadTurbines();\n    }, []);\n\n// return (\n//     <>\n//       <MapContainer ...","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"-----","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"## Part 4: Verify results\n\nRefresh your page and check your console output. You should see all turbines returned, like in the following image:\n\n\n<img src=\"../../src/doc/img/lesson-3/turbines-in-console.png\" width=\"550px\" style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\">","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"-----","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"### Summary\nYou generated mock data, verified counts, and fetched `WindTurbine` records via a CRUD method, preparing data for rendering on the map.","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"<div style=\"display:flex; justify-content:space-between; gap:16px; margin-top:24px; align-items:center; width:100%;\">\n  <a href=\"./02-render-map.c3nb\"\n     aria-label=\"Go to Lesson 1: Render Map\"\n     style=\"display:inline-flex; align-items:center; justify-content:center; padding:10px 16px; border-radius:10px; text-decoration:none; font-weight:600; border:1px solid #d0d7de; background:#f6f8fa; color:#0b1026; box-shadow:0 1px 2px rgba(0,0,0,0.06); transition:transform .15s ease, box-shadow .15s ease;\">\n    ← Previous: Render Map\n  </a>\n  <a href=\"./04-render-turbine-data.c3nb\"\n     aria-label=\"Go to Lesson 3: Render Turbine Data\"\n     style=\"display:inline-flex; align-items:center; justify-content:center; padding:10px 16px; border-radius:10px; text-decoration:none; font-weight:600; border:1px solid #1f6feb; background:#1f6feb; color:#ffffff; box-shadow:0 1px 2px rgba(0,0,0,0.06); transition:transform .15s ease, box-shadow .15s ease;\">\n    Next: Render Turbine Data →\n  </a>\n</div>","output":[],"executionSummary":{}}],"metadata":{"id":"d26f3a5c-0e14-478a-8224-56086725ff33","serializerVersion":"1","runtime":"js-rhino","appName":"academyui"}}